{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\nThe `rebar metrics` subcommand: parses `--since/--until` and `--output json|text`, renders the full metric registry over the range, and is the single entry point wiring the readers. (Date bucketing is intentionally out of scope for this ticket — the command reports each metric over the whole `[since, until]` range; a per-bucket `--bucket` series can be a later additive enhancement and is NOT part of this ticket's contract.)\n\n## Files\n- `src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py` — new: arg parsing + a render loop that evaluates every `MetricSpec` in the registry.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/__init__.py` — wire the `metrics` READ subcommand with a single mechanism: add an explicit `if sub == \"metrics\":` arm in `_dispatch()` (mirroring `init`/`scratch`) that imports `rebar._commands.metrics` and calls its entry point, placed on the reads path that first ensures the store is initialized (as the other read commands are). This is ONE dispatch arm — not a frozenset-membership route (no existing frozenset carries it).\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/metrics.txt` — new help text.\n- `src/rebar/_cli/help/overview.txt` — add the `metrics` line to the subcommand overview.\n- `tests/golden/cli_help/*.out` — regenerate the overview snapshots (`__overview_help.out`, `__overview_dashhelp.out`, and the other overview goldens) and add `metrics__help.out`; the subcommand set is enumerated there.\n- `docs/cli-reference.md` — do NOT hand-edit: it is GENERATED by `scripts/gen_cli_reference.py` (with a CI drift gate). After adding the help/overview text, REGENERATE it (`python scripts/gen_cli_reference.py`) and commit the result.\n- `tests/interfaces/contracts/test_help_overview_coverage.py` — this drift guard checks that every routable subcommand is advertised in the overview and has pinned help text. Its `_routable_subcommands()` unions the dispatch frozensets PLUS an `individual` frozenset listing commands routed by an explicit `if sub == …` arm (`init`, `scratch`, `delete`, `fsck`, …). Because `metrics` is routed by such an explicit arm (not a frozenset), **add `\"metrics\"` to that `individual` frozenset** so `test_routable_set_matches_pinned_help_set` counts it routable; the new `help/metrics.txt` and the `overview.txt` `metrics` line satisfy the pinned-help and advertised-in-overview halves of the guard.\n- `tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py` — new CLI subprocess test.\n\n## Approach\nA thin CLI over the registry keeps the command complete-once: it builds a **context object** and calls `rebar.metrics.registry.evaluate(spec, context)` for every `MetricSpec`, emitting value-or-`unavailable` per metric, so new signals appear with no CLI change.\n\n**REGISTRY hydration (import the PACKAGE, not just registry):** `REGISTRY` is only fully populated after the reader modules run their registration side-effects, and those imports live in `src/rebar/metrics/__init__.py` (which imports `event_metrics`, `git_metrics`, `sidecar_metrics`). Importing `rebar.metrics.registry` ALONE does not trigger them. So `metrics.py` must `import rebar.metrics` (the package — running its `__init__`, which hydrates `REGISTRY`) and then read `rebar.metrics.registry.REGISTRY`. This does NOT breach adapter-isolation: `__init__.py` imports the reader modules but NOT `rebar.metrics.adapters.*`.\n\n**The context object (the contract the readers already expect):** every reader's registered `compute` is a single-arg callable that reads `ctx.repo_root`, `ctx.since`, `ctx.until` (via `getattr(ctx, \"repo_root\", None)` etc.). So `metrics.py` constructs a small context (a dataclass or `SimpleNamespace`) carrying exactly `repo_root` (the resolved store root), `since`, and `until` (the parsed range), and passes it to `evaluate`.\n\n**Adapter isolation (portability guard from 1f77/538c):** `metrics.py` must NOT import any `rebar.metrics.adapters` module. The guard is a **source-level scan**: the test reads `src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py` and asserts its source contains no `rebar.metrics.adapters` import (holds regardless of whether the adapters package exists). Adapter-backed data reaches the command only via `REGISTRY` / the snapshot store, never a direct import.\n\n**Output formats.** JSON (default) is the machine contract: `{\"since\": <str>, \"until\": <str>, \"metrics\": {<id>: {\"lens\",\"source\",\"confidence\",\"value\"} | {\"unavailable\": {\"reason\",\"accruing_since\"}}, ...}}`. `--output text` is a deterministic human summary — one line per metric in registry order: `<id>  [<lens>/<source>]  <value-or-\"unavailable: <reason>\">` (a self-defined layout, NOT borrowed from `rebar audit`). Both formats include every registered metric id.\n\n## Tests\n- CLI (real subprocess against a temp store): `rebar metrics --since ... --until ... --output json` exits 0 and emits a `metrics` map containing every registered id; an unpopulated metric shows `unavailable`; `--output text` lists every metric id.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py` passes: `rebar metrics --since 2026-01-01 --until 2026-07-01 --output json` exits 0 and the emitted `.metrics` map contains an entry for EVERY id in `rebar.metrics.registry.REGISTRY` (asserts `set(output[\"metrics\"].keys()) >= {s.id for s in REGISTRY}` — NOT merely `length > 0`), each entry being either a value (with `source`+`confidence`) or an `unavailable` object with a non-empty `reason`.\n- [ ] `--output text` prints one line per registered metric id (a human summary) — CLI test asserts every id appears and an unavailable metric renders as `unavailable`.\n- [ ] the portability guard holds: a test asserts `src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py`'s source does not import `rebar.metrics.adapters`.\n- [ ] `rebar metrics --help` renders the help file and the command is listed by bare `rebar` — CLI test asserts exit 0 and help contains `--since`.\n- [ ] the golden CLI-help snapshots are regenerated (and `docs/cli-reference.md` via `gen_cli_reference.py`), and the `tests/golden/cli_help` + help-overview-coverage suites pass with `metrics` listed."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784458376589396001,"uuid":"e29a480f-1711-44e0-a68d-a290784eb0ea"}